citations:
    citation-affc-the-queenmaker-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "The Queenmaker"
            text_from_source: "I am no murderer of children. 'Put that away. Myrcella is under my protection. And Ser Arys will permit no harm to come to his precious princess, you know that.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Arianne Martell. Chapter title: The Queenmaker. Arianne has arranged a secret rendezvous at the ruins of Shandystone (an abandoned holdfast in Dorne) with her inner circle: Ser Andrey Dalt (Drey), Spotted Sylva Santagar, Garin (her milk brother, an orphan of the Greenblood), and Ser Gerold Dayne (Darkstar) of High Hermitage. Ser Arys Oakheart arrives with Myrcella Baratheon, whom they plan to crown Queen of the Seven Kingdoms, using Dornish succession law (eldest child inherits regardless of sex). Ser Arys tells Arianne that Tywin Lannister has been murdered by Tyrion, and Cersei has assumed the regency. Arianne muses that her brother Quentyn has been sent across the narrow sea on a secret mission (she found sealed documents with the sun-and-spear of Dorne). Ser Gerold Dayne is described: aquiline nose, silver hair with a streak of black, dark purple eyes, no beard. Quote from Myrcella on Ser Arthur Dayne: 'There was an Arthur Dayne. He was a knight of the Kingsguard in the days of Mad King Aerys.' Gerold responds he is not the Sword of the Morning — 'Men call me Darkstar, and I am of the night.' The party of seven (Arianne, Arys, Myrcella, Drey, Sylva, Garin, Darkstar) sets out by night toward the Greenblood."
